data.text: @EvidenceTroll @henrycooke Yep, that's on my data wishlist, along with comorbidities. But again, privacy. I've read some studies from overseas, would like to see how it stacks up here.
@MakeItSalty @henrycooke Yes, there's quite a bit we only get a summary view of. I'd like to see the vax status of those getting tested.

@EvidenceTroll @henrycooke I knew there was a delay usually (and guessed it was for this reason) when there was 1 or 2 but it seems odd when there's been a larger number announced. The other thing that niggles at me is why isn't waitakere hospital showing in covid hospitalisation numbers?
@MakeItSalty @henrycooke I asked Farrah Hancock about this, deaths are held back in batches, so as not to identify individuals
@henrycooke Have you noticed that the data hasn't been updated on MOH website for the last 6 or 7 deaths reported?

@henrycooke 400 in hospital and 10 in ICU! What are the projected numbers going forward and at what point do we run out of hospital capacity? Conscious there’s a European war and this seems trivial in comparison, but how worried should we be? (Asking for a friend 🤣)
@henrycooke Clearly delta impact unvax'd to a greater degree, but the ratio for Omicrom remains substantial enough to get vaxd.
@henrycooke Think this is an important graph... https://t.co/Agj5mcPOry
@henrycooke What’s it looking like for the 5-11yo pop?
@henrycooke Didn't that Baker dude say the true infections could be up to ten times higher than reported? Wouldn't that mean there could be 2.5% - 24.6% of the population infected?
